.TH GRAFANA-UTIL-WORKSPACE 1 "2026-04-03" "grafana-util 0.9.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
grafana\-util\-workspace \- workspace scan, test, preview, apply, package, and ci workflows
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B grafana-util workspace [\fISUBCOMMAND\fR] [\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
scan, test, preview, package, and apply one local Grafana workspace.
.PP
when you already have a local repo root or staged package and want to understand it, validate it, preview the impact, package it for handoff, or apply a reviewed result.
.SH SUBCOMMANDS
.TP
.B scan
discover what is in one local workspace or staged package.
.TP
.B test
validate whether the local workspace is structurally safe to continue.
.TP
.B preview
show what would change from the current workspace inputs.
.TP
.B apply
turn a reviewed preview into staged or live apply output.
.TP
.B package
package dashboards, alerts, datasources, and metadata into one local handoff artifact.
.TP
.B ci
expose lower\-level contract checks for CI and automation.
